org.net4care.forwarder

Interface FutureResult

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    FutureResultWithAnswer, QueryResult
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    HttpConnector.HttpConnectorFutureResultWithAnswer

    public interface FutureResult
    The result of an asynchronous upload. This is basically a future that eventually will tell whether the upload was successful or not. Inspired by the Netty project.
    Author:
    Henrik Baerbak Christensen, Aarhus University

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void awaitUninterruptibly()
      Waits for this future to be completed without interruption.
      boolean isDone()
      Return true if and only if this future is complete, regardless of whether the operation was successful or failed.
      boolean isSuccess()
      Tell whether the transmission was uploaded successfully.
      String result()
      A description of the upload
